feed.title: MIS1
feed.description:
- Photo Voltaic Panel Temperature
- Solar Radiation
Illuminance & Estimation of the Total Daily Radiation Energy (TDRE) in Wh per square meter in the 550-650nm band (LDR response with a 5% error in the range 25lx-200lx and 90klx-200klx; a 10% error below 25lx and over 200klx and a typical error of 1.5% in the range 200lx-90klx).
In the clear sky scenario the TDRE is about 17% of the Solar Radiation Energy due to the entire Solar Spectrum at sea level.
The illumination is the mean value of several measures, taken about every 0,5s, between two records (about 30s).
- OSC reports the half of the absolute variation/oscillation  (in %) of the illuminance between two records (about 30s), the % is computed to the mean illuminance in that interval, so it is useful to estimate the quality (continuity) of the stored measures.
Valid measures of Temperature and Illuminance from 13-NOV-2011.
Estimation of  the Total Daily Radiation Energy in Wh per square meter in the 550-650nm band from 13-NOV-2011.
Valid measures of OSC from 04-JAN-2012.
Missing data, due to router fault, from 02-JUL-2012 to 21-JUL-2012.
From 24-SEP-2012 data feeding problems ... still working on ...
Feed update restored from 14-OCT-2012.
LDR sensor failure from 04-NOV-2012 to ... (under repair) ... Diagnosis :
LDR failure, the LDR itself isn't working anymore ... looking for a substitute ...
